Paddy Chayevsky's script won an Oscar for Best Original Screenplay; Peter Firth received a posthumous Best Actor award as the unhinged newsman; and Faye Dunaway won Best Actress as a scheming network exec. (Repeat).

programme.title: The Switch
programme.desc: This delightfully offbeat comedy centers on a single woman who decides to conceive via artificial insemination. But seven years later, she reunites with a friend and comes to question the child's paternity after he recalls a last-minute mix-up involving the sperm sample she used. (Repeat).

programme.title: We're Not Married
programme.desc: After a justice of the peace realizes his license has expired, he has to track down the couples he has supposedly married to advise them otherwise. (Repeat).

actor.role: Justice of the Peace Melvin Bush

programme.title: The Best of Everything
programme.desc: A women's-college graduate lands a job at a publishing company run by a high-powered, no-nonsense female executive. (Repeat).

programme.title: He Walked by Night
programme.desc: Fact-based suspenser about a psychopathic burglar who keeps the police off-balance by varying his MO...until he kills a cop. (Repeat).

programme.title: Somewhere in the Night
programme.desc: An amnesiac runs into murder while trying to regain his identity. Complicated plotting, but well-made. (Repeat).

programme.title: On Dangerous Ground
programme.desc: A hardened police officer agrees to help the sister of a killer when she realizes the victim's father hopes to get revenge by murdering the perpetrator, who is deeply mentally ill. (Repeat).

programme.title: Angel Face
programme.desc: An ambulance driver becomes ensnared in the dangerous charm and deadly scheme of a sensuous beauty who is utterly obsessed with murdering her stepmother. (Repeat).

programme.title: Kiss of Death
programme.desc: An ex-con becomes an informer for the assistant DA. Richard Widmark's sinister portrayal of a hoodlum won him acclaim. (Repeat).

programme.title: No Way Out
programme.desc: A bigoted hoodlum is treated by a black intern. (Repeat).

programme.title: A Blueprint for Murder
programme.desc: Tale of a woman suspected of committing murder by poison. Jean Peters. Whitney: Joseph Cotten. Fred: Gary Merrill. Directed by Andrew L. Stone. (Repeat).

programme.title: I Died a Thousand Times
programme.desc: An aging bank robber is released from prison. He decides to pull one last robbery at a high-class mountain resort before retiring, and use some of the loot to pay for a young girl's surgery. Unfortunately the crime doesn't go as planned... (Repeat).(n)

programme.title: Blonde Ice
programme.desc: A society editor (Leslie Brooks) gains position and riches by ruthless murders. Les: Robert Paige. Hack: Walter Sande. Hanneman: John Holland. Mason: Michael Whalen. A lurid one. Directed by Jack Bernhard. (Repeat).(n)

programme.title: Cornered
programme.desc: A World War II veteran hunts down the Nazi collaborators who killed his wife. (Repeat).(n)

programme.title: Born to Be Bad
programme.desc: A manipulative gold digger sets her sights on a wealthy man who's already engaged, ignoring the advances of a rugged writer who loves her despite her flaws. (Repeat).(n)

programme.title: Jail Bait
programme.desc: A doctor is forced to do a plastic-surgery operation to save his son's life. Steve Reeves, Dolores Fuller, Lyle Talbot, Theodora Thurman. (Repeat).(n)

programme.title: The Left Handed Gun
programme.desc: Legendary Old West outlaw Billy the Kid sets out on a rampage, determined to exact revenge on the men responsible for killing his beloved mentor. (Repeat).(n)

programme.title: Tom Horn
programme.desc: Steve McQueen portrays the legendary frontiersman caught up in a range war. Linda Evans, Richard Farnsworth. Joe: Billy Green Bush. Sam: Slim Pickens. Stable Hand: Elisha Cook. William Wiard directed. (Repeat).(n)

programme.title: The Cincinnati Kid
programme.desc: A young poker player hustles in 1930s New Orleans. (Repeat).(n)

programme.title: Now, Voyager
programme.desc: A neurotic, unmarried woman chafing under a domineering mother is helped by an eminent psychiatrist, who instills self-confidence in her, which is put to the test when she falls in love with an unhappily married man. Bette Davis was nominated for Best Actress as the daughter and Gladys Cooper got a Best Supporting Actress nod as her mother. The film's title is from a line in Walt Whitman's "Leaves of Grass." (Repeat).(n)

programme.title: Three Coins in the Fountain
programme.desc: Oscars went to Milton Krasner's location photography and to the title song of this romance about three young American women looking for love in Italy. A Best Picture nominee. (Repeat).(n)

programme.title: Let's Make Love
programme.desc: A billionaire uses a fake name to feign being an actor in order to get into a Broadway show satirizing him, but he winds up falling for the beautiful woman playing opposite him. (Repeat).(n)
